column5: Hi all,  What a perfect evening for a spot of shore fishing. The lake was like glass which usually results in slow to terrible fishing...but the bite was almost non stop for the one and a half hours i was there....lots of little walleye, a few decent keeper size and 2 or 3 18" +.                            <iframe width="420" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/HxhUnAkNbS4" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
Great stuff Simon!! Nothing like a pickeral Thanksgiving supper ..
I watched the whole video. I didn't think it would ever end. haha. Nice work.
u caught more walleye in 1.5 hours than I did for my whole friggin life...
A perfect primer to a full day of fishing... And I'm off.
Wow!  Some amazing pictures there!  Gotta love fall fishing!  Always enjoy your videos too  Oh yeah....nice fish!
I like your spot Simon Got to love when the fishes are biting Great report, pics and video  How far is the lake from your house?
